This paper deals with natural language processing and robotics, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) since the paper focuses on converting natural language instructions into a form that a robot can understand. The paper also involves machine learning and reasoning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with robotics, which suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Automation). The paper also involves training a language model, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the paper involves observing objects in the environment, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
